Below is one way to “parse” the rocket‐shaped model into layers and then match each layer’s blocks to the dictionary images without rotating them.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE TARGET STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  Total Block Count: 10  
•  Layers (Bottom to Top):
   ▸ Layer 1 (Bottom): Three green blocks side‐by‐side forming a long base.  
   ▸ Layer 2: Centered red arch flanked on the left and right by orange wedge blocks.  
   ▸ Layer 3: Two cubes side by side—green on the left, blue on the right.  
   ▸ Layer 4 (Top): Two orange wedges meeting at a peak to form the “roof.”  

•  Spatial Notes:  
   – Each of the three green blocks on the bottom sits flush in a row (left, center, right).  
   – The red arch (oriented front‐to‐back) stands in the middle of the second layer; one orange wedge sits to its left and another to its right, all resting on the green base.  
   – Above the arch/wedges are two cubes (green left, blue right).  
   – Finally, a pair of orange wedges (one left, one right) forms the peaked roof.  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING DICTIONARY BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below are the dictionary indices that match each needed piece exactly as shown (no rotation):

•  Bottom Layer (three green rectangles):  
   – Use block #9 three times (green block lying horizontally).  

•  Second Layer:  
   – Red arch in the center: use block #1.  
   – Left orange wedge: use block #14.  
   – Right orange wedge: use block #16.  

•  Third Layer (two cubes):  
   – Green cube on the left: block #8.  
   – Blue cube on the right: block #7.  

•  Top Layer (two orange wedges):  
   – Left roof wedge: block #14.  
   – Right roof wedge: block #16.  

Hence the full “bill of materials” is:  
•  #9 × 3  
•  #1 × 1  
•  #14 × 2  
•  #16 × 2  
•  #8 × 1  
•  #7 × 1  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Use the following move sequence (one block per step):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 9        // Bottom left green
  Step2: Move block with index 9        // Bottom center green
  Step3: Move block with index 9        // Bottom right green
  Step4: Move block with index 14       // Second-layer left orange wedge
  Step5: Move block with index 1        // Red arch in the center
  Step6: Move block with index 16       // Second-layer right orange wedge
  Step7: Move block with index 8        // Third-layer green cube (left)
  Step8: Move block with index 7        // Third-layer blue cube (right)
  Step9: Move block with index 14       // Top-layer left orange wedge
  Step10: Move block with index 16      // Top-layer right orange wedge
}

That sequence (from the base upward) reproduces the rocket‐shaped model exactly as pictured.
